  "text": "The following primers were used [CITATION_1] : spacer region-specific primers, spacer region 33 specific (5′ACACCGACATGACGGCGG3′) and spacer region 34 specific (5′CGACGGTGTGGGCGAGG3′); IS6110 (5′GGACAACGCCGAATTGCG′3 and 5′TAGGCGTCGGTGACAAAGGCCAC′3), and Mycobacterium genus-specific TB11 (sequence 5′ACCAACGATGGTGTGTCCAT3′) and TB12 (sequence 5′CTTGTCGAACCGCATACCCT3′). Expected PCR products are 550, 439, and 172 and 99 bp, respectively. PCR mixtures contained 20 μl of 2× PCR mix, 10 μL of primer mix with each primer at 0.66 pmol/μL, 0.2 μL of Taq polymerase enzyme (Roche Diagnostics), and 10 μL of extracted DNA. The PCR conditions were 95°C for 3 min; 30 cycles of 95°C for 20 s, 65°C for 30 s, and 72°C for 30 s; and 72°C for 7 min. After PCR, the products were analyzed by electrophoresis in agarose gel.",
